## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="b7ba2-281">O exemplo a seguir cria uma gramática de reconhecimento de fala que possa reconhecer as duas frases, "tornar o plano de fundo *cor*" e "Definir plano de fundo *cor*", onde *cor* é selecionado em um conjunto de cores.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b7ba2-281">The following example creates a speech recognition grammar that can recognize the two phrases, "Make background *color*" and "Set background to *color*", where *color* is selected from a set of colors.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b7ba2-282">Vários tipos são usados para construir a gramática final, como [cadeia de caracteres](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=159733), <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices>, e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b7ba2-282">Various types are used to build the final grammar, such as [String](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=159733), <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices>, and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="b7ba2-283">Os operadores de conversão explícita em chamadas para o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder.Add%2A> métodos são opcionais.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="b7ba2-283">The explicit cast operators in the calls to the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder.Add%2A> methods are optional.</span></span>  
  
